The room ahead seemed quite large, perhaps larger than any Cody had encountered so far. With a clear passageway in front of
him, Cody kept the pole sickle pointed a little higher, so that parrying a weapon from either side would be a fraction of a
second faster. Lulu was no longer alongside him, but Cody comforted himself with the thought that she was as much a tripping
hazard to any enemy as she was to him.
